# Handover

When I say we're "done for the day" (or ask for a handover), write a thorough handover file.

## Where
- Folder: `.context/handover/` (gitignored).
- New file each time, never overwritten: `.context/handover/YYYY-MM-DD-handover.md`.
- If multiple in one day, append `-2`, `-3`, etc.

## Goal
A new chat should be fully caught up by reading ONLY this file. Be thorough and explicit - over-explain rather than assume prior knowledge.

## Required sections
```markdown
# Handover - YYYY-MM-DD

## Project state
Current high-level status of the project.

## What we accomplished
Detailed list of what was done (reference work-log entries).

## In progress / unfinished
What's partially done and where it stands.

## Next steps
Concrete, ordered next actions.

## Open decisions / questions
Anything awaiting a decision.

## How to run / setup notes
Commands, env, gotchas needed to continue.

## Key files & locations
Important files and what they do.
```
